{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaa1fafe2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3371"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3371"},"text":"§ 3371.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Undefinitized contractual actions: required description of anticipated effect on military department requirements if use of undefinitized contractual action results in delay","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The head of an agency may not enter into an undefinitized contractual action unless the request to the head of the agency for authorization of the contractual action includes a description of the anticipated effect on requirements of the military department concerned if a delay is incurred for purposes of determining contractual terms, specifications, and price before performance is begun under the contractual action.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaa1fafe3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added and amended ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dA/tXVIII/s1819/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title XVIII, § 1819(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4189"},"text":"134 Stat. 4189","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idaa1fafe4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idaa1fafe5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idaa1fafe6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":n